    40→/**
    41→ * <p>Manages the request creation and response handling for the heartbeat. The module creates a
    42→ * heartbeat request using the state stored in the membership manager and enqueues it to
    43→ * the network queue to be sent out. Once the response is received, it updates the state in the
    44→ * membership manager and handles any errors.
    45→ *
    46→ * <p>The heartbeat manager generates heartbeat requests based on the member state. It's also responsible
    47→ * for the timing of the heartbeat requests to ensure they are sent according to the heartbeat interval
    48→ * (while the member state is stable) or on demand (while the member is acknowledging an assignment or
    49→ * leaving the group).
    50→ *
    51→ * <p>If the member got kicked out of a group, it will try to give up the current assignment by invoking {@code
    52→ * OnPartitionsLost} before attempting to join again with a zero epoch.
    53→ *
    54→ * <p>If the coordinator not is not found, we will skip sending the heartbeat and try to find a coordinator first.
    55→ *
    56→ * <p>When the member completes the assignment reconciliation, the {@link HeartbeatRequestState} will be reset so
    57→ * that a heartbeat will be sent in the next event loop.
    58→ *
    59→ * <p>The class variable R is the response for the specific group's heartbeat RPC.
    60→ */
